name: $property
desc: Returns: A reference to an element that holds a coded value that corresponds to a code system property. The idea is that the information model carries an element somewhere that is labeled to correspond with a code system property.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: A reference to an element that holds a coded value that corresponds to a code system property. The idea is that the information model carries an element somewhere that is labeled to correspond with a code system property.

name: $system
desc: Returns: An absolute URI that identifies the code system of the dependency code (if the source/dependency is a value set that crosses code systems).

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: An absolute URI that identifies the code system of the dependency code (if the source/dependency is a value set that crosses code systems).

name: $value
desc: Returns: Identity (code or path) or the element/item/ValueSet/text that the map depends on / refers to.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Identity (code or path) or the element/item/ValueSet/text that the map depends on / refers to.

name: $display
desc: Returns: The display for the code. The display is only provided to help editors when editing the concept map.
